      "message": "@chungpo1020@gmail.com\n\nI have did following validation \n\n1. With the patch, LANplus (non-system interface) parsing is correct and matches expected field alignment.\n\n   * ipmitool -I lanplus -H 127.0.0.1 -p 2623 -U root -P 0penBmc raw 0x04 0x02 0x04 0x01 0x01 0x01 0x59 0x01 0x00\n\n   * ipmid[308]: PlatformEvent: eventRevision\u003d4, sensorType\u003d1, sensorNumber\u003d1, eventDirectionType\u003d1, data0\u003d89\n\n2.When I tested from BMC console (with patch) using the System Interface-style payload, it failed in my setup.\n\n   * root@romulus:~# ipmitool raw 0x04 0x02 0x21 0x04 0x01 0x01 0x01 0x59 0x01 0x00\nUnable to send RAW command (channel\u003d0x0 netfn\u003d0x4 lun\u003d0x0 cmd\u003d0x2 rsp\u003d0xc7): Request data length invalid\nroot@romulus:~#\n\n3.After reverting the patch, that BMC-console command succeeded and fields aligned for that payload format.\n\n   * ipmitool raw 0x04 0x02 0x21 0x04 0x01 0x01 0x01 0x59 0x01 0x00\n\n   * PlatformEvent: eventRevision\u003d4, sensorType\u003d1, sensorNumber\u003d1, eventDirectionType\u003d1, data0\u003d89\n\nNote: Just My doubt is After New implementation previous behavior also should work right? correct me if I am wrong. Thanks",
